This is the Backend for a Project Management Application. Only the server side
The overall system has two components: Server, and Web Version (Frontend).
The Client (frontend) also exists as separate project
This project focuses only on the Backend (Server).
The Web Admin Panel should include the following features:
1. User Management:
Roles:
    Planning Cell/Project Directorate
    Project Director (PD)
    XEN / SDO (RRE)
    SE / CE (RRE)
    Admin / IT Cell
Department:
    Both
    Construction / GSC
    Field Divisions
    HQ
    Corporate
Permissions:
    Add Business Plan Projects
    Approve Project Initiation
    Update progress, enter actual cost, upload photos
    Monitor progress, approve completions
    Manage users, roles, templates

User management will be a role based user management. With full control on viewing, inserting, editing, deleting in forms.
The login will be with username and password. Keep it dynamic so it's scalable. 

Populate minimalistic one or two row data in tables to test functionalities. 


Profile:
Region, Division and site. 
These will be three profiles for area classifications. Region will be on top level. each region contain multiple divisions and each division contain multiple sites. so make sure to link them with foreign keys. 


This project will be using Shadcn UI as design components library, tailwind if necessary. Next JS and Typescript. Use postgres for database.

Keep fields in all tables minimalistic so we won't clutter things up

Use a proper separation of concern architecture used with Next JS projects. But do not over complicate it. 